New measures coming into effect at bars and restaurants. From Monday to Saturday, they won't be allowed to sell booze after 6pm. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - New measures coming into effect at bars and restaurants. From Monday to Saturday, they won't be allowed to sell booze after 6pm. READ: What should you do if you think you have COVID-19? On Sunday's, no alcohol sales after 1pm. That's one of the latest measures being put in place to stem the spread of COVID-19. Restaurants may also only have a maximum of 50 people at any given time. President Cyril Ramaphosa confirmed on Thursday, the number of people infected has risen to 150. READ: Reserve Bank cuts repo rate by full percentage point Meanwhile, China has recorded no new locally transmitted cases of COVID-19. But, it has imported 34 cases, mainly from Spain and Britain. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.